commits.message:
loader.js: Really don't push redirects to history

refs #4879

loader.js: Don't consider redirected form submits as auto submits

A redirect caused by a form submit is **never** an automatic submit.
Unless I'm missing something here. There is one way this may be true,
as ipl forms without a submit button are indeed successful due to a
autosubmit element, but they don't redirect by default. So if the
controller redirects in such a case, the form should have a submit
button, I guess..

Anyway, this is necessary due to the previous commit as this may
otherwise cause form submits, that re-render layout during a redirect,
are considered being auto submitted. (Such as the login form)

Response: Only preserve `showCompact` for explicit redirects

In case of a `__SELF__` redirect, the client should still have
the parameter in the location and its preserved this way then.

Fix redirection loop (#5143)

fixes #5133

issue.title: check in MigrationManager.php not compatible with postgresql
issue.body:
## Describe the bug
In the web interface I get an error
SQLSTATE[22023]: Invalid parameter value: 7 ERROR: unrecognized privilege type: "CREATE", query was: SELECT has_table_privilege(:user, :table, :privilege) AS table_privilege_granted
PostgreSQL doesn't have the CREATE privilege.

In the postgres log I see: 
`2023-09-27 09:09:54.232 UTC [4154218] icinga2@icinga2 ERROR:  unrecognized privilege type: "CREATE"
2023-09-27 09:09:54.232 UTC [4154218] icinga2@icinga2 STATEMENT:  SELECT has_table_privilege($1, $2, $3) AS table_privilege_granted
`

I removed 'CREATE' in the  public function getRequiredDatabasePrivileges() in /usr/share/php/Icinga/Application/MigrationManager.php
return ['CREATE','SELECT','INSERT','UPDATE','DELETE','DROP','ALTER','CREATE VIEW','INDEX','EXECUTE'];
-> return ['SELECT','INSERT','UPDATE','DELETE','DROP','ALTER','CREATE VIEW','INDEX','EXECUTE'];
which fixed the problem for me. I leave it up to someone else to find a more generic solution.

## To Reproduce

1.In the web interface an error occurs when clicking on the settings icon -> system -> migrate


## Expected behavior
Status screen

## Screenshots
If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.
![image](https://github.com/Icinga/icingaweb2/assets/15324030/6654d608-7222-416d-bed3-8846c1020504)


## Your Environment
Include as many relevant details about the environment you experienced the problem in

* Icinga Web 2 version and modules (System - About): 2.12.0
* Web browser used: Firefox
* Icinga 2 version used (`icinga2 --version`): r2.14.0-1
* PHP version used (`php --version`): 8.1.2-1ubuntu2.14
* Server operating system and version: Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS
*  Database: Postgres 14

## Additional context
--

comment.body:
Finally tracked it down. The `showCompact` parameter was only a part of the problem. The actual problem was that aborted redirects were pushed to history. Something that should have been solved with #4879 but got broke by 9dd21841a39796764a07a19fbb5626a21d3118c6.

Big thanks to @ctrlaltca! Your request dumps and own debugging helped me a lot.
